```javascript
async function checkRequirements() {
  const requiredCommands = ["wget", "tar"];
  const missingCommands = [];

  // Check if each required command exists
  await Promise.all(requiredCommands.map(async (command) => {
    const exists = await commandExists(command);
    if (!exists) {
      missingCommands.push(command);
    }
  }));

  // If any required command is missing, throw an error
  if (missingCommands.length > 0) {
    const missingCommandsString = missingCommands.join(", ");
    throw new Error(`Missing required commands: ${missingCommandsString}.`);
  }
}
```

By breaking down the logic into separate steps and using clear variable names, the code becomes easier to understand and maintain.
